Job Title: Director, Research & Labs, Data Standards and Excellence
Ad Text:
CSL's R&D organization is accelerating innovation to deliver greater impact for patients. With a project-led structure and a focus on collaboration, we’re building a future-ready team that thrives in dynamic biotech ecosystems. Joining CSL now means being part of an agile team committed to developing therapies that make a meaningful difference worldwide.




Reporting to the Executive Director, R&D Data Excellence lead you will be responsible for defining, implementing, and maintaining data standards and governance frameworks across research and laboratory environments. This role ensures high-quality, interoperable, and FAIR (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, Reusable) data to support scientific discovery, digital innovation, and regulatory readiness. 




This role has accountability across the R&D and the Technical Operations teams to ensure that data enables the R&D Submission and the Technology Transfer cycle time and milestone targets.  In addition, this role has accountability for working with the Search team to identify opportunities and obstacles in external collaborations and acquisitions. 




Your Responsibilities




Develop and maintain data standards for research and lab-generated data, such as assay data, instrument outputs, and metadata, ensuring consistency across platforms and teams

Establish governance frameworks to ensure consistent data capture, annotation, and integration across digital systems (e.g., ELNs, LIMS, data lakes)

Collaborate with scientists, lab managers, IT, and data stewards to embed data standards into lab workflows and digital systems, supporting seamless data integration and usage

Monitor compliance with established data standards, identifying opportunities for improvement and driving continuous quality enhancements

Represent the organization in external data standards bodies and consortia (e.g., Allotrope, FAIR sharing, Pistoia Alliance) to ensure alignment with global data standards and best practices

Support data quality, lineage, and traceability efforts, enabling the use of data for advanced analytics, AI/ML applications, and regulatory submissions

Provide training, guidance, and support to internal teams on data standards, ontologies, and governance best practices to ensure consistent adoption across the organization




Your Qualifications & Experience




Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Life Sciences, Bioinformatics, Data Science, or a related field

12+ years of experience in research data management, lab informatics, or data governance

Must have experience working within Research and Life sciences

Strong knowledge of scientific data standards (e.g., Allotrope, AnIML, ISA-Tab), ontologies (e.g., OBI, ChEBI), and metadata frameworks

Must have sound experience working within a AI digital strategy team setting

Experience with lab systems (e.g., ELN, LIMS, CDS) and data integration platforms

Excellent communication, stakeholder engagement, and documentation skills, with the ability to influence and guide teams on data governance best practices




Melbourne CBD, Hybrid Working

If you’re passionate about enabling world-class research through data, apply now!

Job Title: Principal Data (AI) Platform Engineer - Contract - Sydney
Ad Text:
We’re seeking an experienced Principal Data (AI) Platform Engineer  to join a large-scale technology transformation program for one of our clients in Sydney.

This is a 'hands on' role requiring writing code, building infrastructure, and implementing the platform. 

This is a 12 month contract role initially with a view to extend working on a critical technology program across their Data and AI strategy to enable tooling and streamline workflows at enterprise level. 

The role offers hybrid working with 3 days in the office.                 
           
Key Responsibilities:

Lead the technical build and operationalisation of the AI platform, working with the data team to meet the requirements.
Driving monthly releases and the the implementations to align with the key strategy.
Establish and monitor platform performance in line with SLAs.
Provide technical leadership and architecture and produce detailed technical designs.
Support AI roadmap planning, execution of sprints, and contribute to agile scrums.
Work collaboratively with the tech and business teams to ensure continuous improvement including AWS cloud Engineers. 
  Requirements:

 8-10 years of experience in designing, building, and operating complex Data  platforms in large enterprise environments
Strong experience in building AI platforms in an enterprise organisation.
Expertise in cloud-native infrastructure development including AWS.
Experience with SageMaker, Bedrock, S3, IAM, and other DevOps tools.
Strong experience working in a greenfield environment for AI.
Experience in designing, implementing AI/ML platforms.
Hands-on experience with infrastructure-as-code (e.g., Terraform, CloudFormation)
Experience with CI/CD pipelines for deploying and managing platform components. 
Strong leadership experience and ability to mentor technical teams. 
Experience with prompt engineering and LLM orchestration, and GenAI  is highly desirable
Strong communication skills and ability to work under pressure to SLAs.
Ability to work with cross-functional teams in a collaborative environment to achieve success. 
Certifications in AWS or  DevOps/ML Ops technologies.
You must have full working rights in Australia to apply for this role.

Ad Text:
Permanent, Full Time

Build the integration layer for a digitally connected city.

LET’S EXPLORE THE JOB

Our progressive Information Technology team are looking for an Integration Specialist who wants to do more than keep systems running, someone who wants to design the platform that connects everything.

In this role, you will own how critical systems communicate across Council. You’ll architect scalable, secure integrations, shape standards, and help modernise our technology ecosystem so we can deliver smarter services to a rapidly growing community.

If you enjoy solving complex integration challenges, influencing architecture, and working on technology that has visible impact, this is the role for you.

Your key focus areas are:

Architect, build, and maintain enterprise integration solutions across multiple platforms

Design API-led integrations and automated workflows

Collaborate with stakeholders to translate business needs into technical solutions

Monitor, troubleshoot, and optimise integration performance and reliability

Read the position statement and learn more about this exciting opportunity.

LET’S HEAR ABOUT YOU

You’re a technically strong integration professional who enjoys connecting complex systems and seeing your solutions deliver real-world outcomes.

You combine deep hands-on experience with the ability to influence stakeholders and guide technical direction.

You likely have experience in environments where reliability, security, and scalability matter, and you’re motivated by building solutions that stand the test of time.

Specifically, you will bring:

Degree-level qualifications in Computer Science or a related field and/or demonstrated experience delivering real integration solutions

Enterprise integration platforms or middleware

Microsoft Azure Integration Services (highly regarded)

Boomi, Power Platform (Power Automate/RPA), or similar tools

Data formats such as JSON and XML

Experience delivering complex multi-system integrations

35-hour work week

Hybrid working arrangements and flexible hours

9-day fortnight

Supportive leadership and career development opportunities

We have a flexible workplace and focus on all aspects of your physical and mental health and safety. We want you to be with us for the long term, so providing you with rich career experiences and ongoing development is our priority.

Work in one of the most picturesque regions of NSW, with the natural beauty of Lake Macquarie right on your doorstep.

Along with many other perks that come from choosing Lake Mac!

CHOOSE THE LAKE MAC WAY

We know it is our people that will shape the future of our city. That’s why we’re passionate about providing a workplace that empowers our staff to be creative, innovative and bold. When you join the team at Lake Macquarie City Council, you’re joining a group of people with a commitment to make our city even better. We’re proud of our city and the work we do, and we know you will be too.

We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive workforce. Overview


The Azure Core Trusted Platform team safeguards Microsoft’s foundational cloud infrastructure by ensuring that our engineering systems, services, and workflows meet the highest bars for security, privacy, and regulatory compliance. Microsoft runs on trust, and we build the platform‑level capabilities that make safe‑by‑default, compliant engineering possible across Azure, embedding transparency, traceability, and automated safeguards directly into how engineers build and operate services.

Our work increasingly leverages AI through agentic workflows, intelligent automation, and privacy‑aware generation and validation to solve traditionally complex compliance and safety challenges in scalable, creative ways.

As a Software Engineer on the team, you’ll work deeply in distributed systems, reliability, debugging, secure coding, cloud security, automation, and CI/CD, applying strong engineering fundamentals to build resilient, compliant platform components used across Microsoft.

Privacy Manager is a core part of this mission, providing the unified platform that helps hundreds of Microsoft engineering teams understand, track, and confidently manage how their services use, store, and move data. It brings together automated data‑flow insights, privacy‑aware tooling, and structured review workflows that make compliance easier to adopt and harder to get wrong. By integrating these capabilities directly into engineering processes, Privacy Manager enables teams to make informed decisions, reduce risk, and meet evolving global regulatory expectations without slowing down innovation.If you’re excited by the intersection of large‑scale systems, compliance engineering, and AI‑powered innovation, you’ll find a team that values curiosity, impact, and building the trusted foundations Microsoft and its customers rely on.

Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.

Responsibilities

Understanding User Requirements: Partner with product, security, privacy, and other stakeholders to determine and translate customer and user needs into feature requirements, continuously improving solutions based on user insights.

Design & Architecture: Support identification of dependencies and contribute to architecture and feature design by evaluating options, developing design documents with oversight, and ensuring scalability, security, and testability through cross‑team collaboration.

AI‑Native Development: Use AI tools responsibly across the software development lifecycle, validating and reviewing AI‑generated changes with strong engineering discipline.

Coding & Implementation: With guidance, create and implement high‑quality, secure, and maintainable code by reusing existing components where applicable; break down work items into tasks, provide estimates, and execute features safely, including managing deployments, rollbacks, and experiments using flighting and metrics.

Engineering Excellence: Apply secure design principles, improve tooling and automation, enforce security and compliance standards, and drive consistent, high‑quality engineering practices.

Reliability & Supportability: Act as a Designated Responsible Individual (DRI) for simple issues by monitoring systems, product features, or services for degradation, downtime, or interruptions; follow established playbooks to recommend and execute recovery actions.

Live‑Site Operations: Support live‑site operations through on‑call rotations, resolve incidents, and maintain reliable services by improving monitoring, telemetry, and operational readiness.

Continuous Improvement: Review current developments and proactively seek new knowledge to improve the availability, reliability, efficiency, observability, and performance of products while driving consistency in monitoring and operations at scale.

Qualifications

Required Qualifications:

Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science, or related technical discipline with proven experience coding in languages including, but not limited to, C, C++, C#, Java, JavaScript, or Python

OR equivalent experience.

1+ years of expereince in the relevant fields mentioned. 

Other Requirements:

Ability to meet Microsoft, customer and/or government security screening requirements are required for this role. These requirements include, but are not limited to the following specialized security screenings: 

Microsoft Cloud Background Check: This position will be required to pass the Microsoft Cloud Background Check upon hire/transfer and every two years thereafter.

Preferred Qualifications:

Master's Degree in Computer Science or related technical field with proven experience coding in languages including, but not limited to, C, C++, C#, Java, JavaScript, or Python

OR Bachelor's Degree in Computer Science or related technical field AND 2+ years technical engineering experience with coding in languages including, but not limited to, C, C++, C#, Java, JavaScript, or Python

OR equivalent experience.

#EiP

This position will be open for a minimum of 5 days, with applications accepted on an ongoing basis until the position is filled.

Ad Text:
The role:

As the Data Engineer, you will play a pivotal role in ensuring the stability, performance, and continual improvement of the Digital Delivery Portal (DDP) data platform following its recent uplift to a modern Azure data lakehouse architecture.

Working within the Portfolio Reporting & Analytics team, you will be responsible for the operational support, maintenance and optimisation of a complex multi‑layered data environment that includes Azure Data Factory ingestion pipelines, Databricks, Azure SQL databases, and an API layer built on Azure App Services.

Your responsibilities will include:

Monitoring and maintaining data ingestion pipelines across SharePoint, Microsoft Project, Azure SQL and the data lakehouse.
Managing Delta Lake structures, incremental data processing, and schema evolution to ensure data quality and reliability.
Ensuring the performance, security and accuracy of APIs supporting the DDP platform.
Supporting and optimising Power BI semantic models and Databricks SQL Warehouse connections.
Troubleshooting operational issues and identifying opportunities for system improvements, automation and optimisation.
Working collaboratively with analysts, vendors, stakeholders and project teams to maintain the platform's integrity and support emerging reporting and data needs.

This role is critical to ensuring that the data platform continues to operate effectively, remains scalable, and provides high‑quality, trusted data to eHealth Queensland.

Is this the opportunity for you?

If you are passionate about ensuring the stability and performance of modern cloud data platforms, this is an excellent opportunity to apply your skills in a complex, high‑impact environment.

You will thrive in this role if you:

Have strong experience with Azure Data Factory, Databricks, Delta Lake, SQL, and cloud‑based data engineering.
Enjoy diagnosing issues, improving reliability, and optimising data pipelines and platform performance.
Understand how to maintain and refine multi‑layer data architectures, including landing, bronze, silver and gold layers.
Bring a continuous improvement mindset to evolving data models, ingestion patterns and operational processes.
Are comfortable working with APIs, CI/CD pipelines, and enterprise data governance tools such as Unity Catalog.
Value collaboration and can partner effectively with analysts, vendors, and business stakeholders.

eHealth Queensland is one of the largest Information Communication Technology operations in the state. It is responsible for ensuring the smooth operation of information systems and technologies so that Queensland Health employees and health providers have access to information that supports the delivery of health care.

Benefits of working with eHealth Queensland:

By joining eHealth Queensland, you will work within a fast-paced, challenging and supportive environment where every employee plays a critical role in our ongoing success.

You will enjoy a variety of benefits, including:

Competitive salary + generous superannuation and leave loading
Flexible working arrangements
Diverse work culture
Career training and development

To apply for this exciting opportunity, submit your resume and a short statement (maximum 2 pages) on how your experience, abilities, knowledge and personal qualities are relevant for the role, taking into account the key responsibilities and attributes noted in the ‘How you will be assessed' section of the role description.

About Us

Future Secure AI is a rapidly scaling AI company co‑developed with one of the world’s largest financial institutions. Operating with the agility of a startup and the backing of global enterprise leaders, we are building technology that elevates human performance through advanced AI Co-workers and next‑generation LLM systems.

With deep C‑suite access across industries and a growing network of global partners, our mission is bold: to redefine how humans and AI collaborate—and deliver 10x outcomes for individuals and organisations.

We are growing fast and looking for exceptional talent to help shape the future of AI.

The Opportunity

As a Staff Data Scientist, you will be a key technical leader within our advanced analytics and AI group. You will design, build, and deploy sophisticated machine learning systems—particularly LLM‑driven solutions—that solve high‑value, real‑world problems for enterprise clients.

You’ll be part of a culture that prizes technical excellence, creativity, and continuous learning. Beyond technical depth, you will influence strategy, mentor emerging talent, and help shape our approach to responsible and scalable AI.

Your work will directly contribute to AI systems that have the potential to transform industries—and society.

What You’ll Do

Architect, build, and deploy machine learning models and LLM systems that drive meaningful impact for our products and users

Analyse complex, large‑scale structured and unstructured datasets to uncover insights and opportunities

Enhance LLM output quality across diverse use cases, including optimisation of multi‑step reasoning chains

Lead MLOps initiatives including model performance tracking, benchmark design, quality assurance, and compliance

Influence long‑term data and AI strategy, including governance, ethical AI, and scalable frameworks

Collaborate closely with engineering, product, and executive stakeholders to deliver innovative, production‑ready solutions

Mentor and uplift junior data scientists, setting standards for excellence

About You

You are a seasoned Data Scientist (8+ years) with deep hands‑on experience and a track record of delivering impactful ML and AI outcomes. You thrive in ambiguity, communicate exceptionally well, and enjoy partnering with cross‑functional teams to deliver measurable results.

You balance scientific rigour with practical execution, and you bring a curiosity that keeps you constantly exploring new research—especially in the fast‑moving LLM space.

You’ll be successful if you have:

A Master’s or Doctorate in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Computer Science or a related discipline

Demonstrated history of completing high‑impact data science projects, ideally in complex or high‑stakes environments

Strong experience with NLP techniques: LSTMs, CNNs, transformers, topic modelling, supervised NLP

Commercial experience with modern LLM ecosystems (e.g., LangChain, LlamaIndex, RAG pipelines, multi‑agent frameworks, GPT‑based systems)

Advanced SQL and 2+ years of Python experience focused on machine learning and NLP

Ability to translate complex technical concepts into clear, actionable insights for non‑technical stakeholders

Empathy, humility, and a growth mindset—open to feedback and committed to collaboration

Ability to stay at the frontier of LLM research, applying new developments pragmatically

Comfort working in an agile, fast‑evolving environment

Ability to attend our Sydney CBD office 1–2 days per week

Why Join Us?

Shape the future of AI alongside world‑class technical and commercial leaders

Work with cutting‑edge models, frameworks, and R&D pipelines

Contribute to solutions used by global enterprises

Grow rapidly in a company with significant backing and momentum

Join a high‑trust, high‑performance culture built around craft, ownership, and impact

If you’re driven by innovation, inspired by big challenges, and ready to build AI systems that matter—we’d love to meet you.

For a quicker response, we encourage you to apply directly through our website at https://www.futuresecure.ai/. There, you can watch a video about AI workers and explore the career opportunities we have available.

Based at either our Melbourne Burwood or Geelong Waterfront Campus, hybrid work available 
Fulltime and continuing

This role blends deep hands-on technical capability with solution design leadership and stakeholder engagement.

As a senior hands-on engineering role, you will have accountability for the solution design and technical quality. You will act as a key technical authority for complex AI implementations, guiding approaches, supporting other engineers and developing and translating requirements into robust, production-ready solutions.

You will:

Design and deliver advanced full-stack AI-enabled applications aligned to strategic priorities
Embed security, privacy, accessibility and responsible AI principles by design
Integrate ML, GenAI and vector database capabilities into scalable enterprise solutions
Champion modern engineering, MLOps and data management practices
Lead automation, CI/CD and operational practices to support stable production environments
Translate complex business needs into intuitive, user-centred digital experiences
Collaborate across engineering, data, product and operations teams to move solutions from prototype to production
Provide technical guidance and code-level support to other engineers on architecture, implementation and troubleshooting
Define and refine reusable patterns, reference implementations and technical standards

 

About you

You are an experienced AI or full-stack specialist who thrives in complex environments and enjoys solving meaningful problems. Most importantly, you combine technical depth with strong communication skills, enabling you to influence stakeholders and contribute to a culture of innovation, inclusion and continuous improvement.

You’ll bring:

Experience with cloud platforms and modern full-stack development
Strong capability in Python and FastAPI for scalable APIs and microservices
Experience integrating and deploying ML/GenAI models and working with vector databases
Knowledge of RESTful APIs, GraphQL and WebSockets
Experience with React (Vite and Material UI)
Understanding of authentication and authorisation (OAuth2, JWT)
A track record delivering secure, production-grade AI or data-driven applications
Experience reviewing code, guiding design decisions and supporting other engineers in complex implementations
Comfort acting as the primary technical problem-solver for difficult engineering challenges

Company: Department of Environment, Tourism, Science and Innovation
Ad Text:
Join DETSI as a Scientific Data Engineer.
The Department of the Environment, Tourism, Science and Innovation (DETSI) is seeking a highly skilled Scientific Data Engineer to lead the transformation of our data management, analysis, and delivery capabilities. This is a unique opportunity to drive the technical innovation that supports Queensland's environmental, scientific, and business objectives.

About the Role:
As a Scientific Data Engineer with DETSI, you'll play a pivotal role in enhancing the Department's data maturity and capabilities. This position will include team leadership responsibilities for a suitable candidate.

Working within the Information and Digital Science Delivery team, you'll be responsible for accelerating systems, delivering innovative solutions, and improving information accessibility. Through your leadership and expertise, you'll enable DETSI to align with FAIR data principles (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, Reusable), meeting both scientific and business needs.

Key Responsibilities:
- Design, build, and enhance data pipelines and models to ensure consistent, high quality data collection and usage.
- Lead problem-solving initiatives by developing innovative solutions that address complex challenges in data architecture and governance.
- Deliver expert guidance to the development of ETL/ELT processes, enabling timely and reliable access to data for departmental use.
- Provide technical mentoring and leadership to build data engineering capabilities across DETSI teams.
- Ensure all data products meet governance and quality compliance requirements while adhering to best practices.
- Collaborate across teams and stakeholders to develop relationships, foster teamwork, and deliver impactful solutions.
- Foster a workplace culture that supports and promotes the interests of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and actively engage through our work to contribute to better outcomes for First Nations peoples of Australia.

What We're Looking For:
To excel in this role, you'll bring:
- Proven experience in ETL/ELT data processes, modelling data structures, and linking business intelligence systems. Experience with scientific and geo-spatial data is highly valued.
- Strong technical skills in tools such as SQL, Python, Power BI, Databricks, R and modern cloud platforms (e.g., Azure).
- A demonstrated ability to rapidly acquire knowledge about science data management tasks and accessibility best practices.
- Experience in data governance, organisational change, and shaping procedures that align with industry standards.
- Excellent teamwork skills with the ability to motivate and lead in complex, rapidly changing environments.
- High-level written and verbal communication skills, including stakeholder engagement and negotiation abilities.
- The ability to prioritise tasks, meet deadlines, and implement improvements to workflows and systems.

Location:
The preferred location for this role is Dutton Park, but consideration will be given to DETSI regional offices, subject to availability.

Apply Now:
If you're passionate about data innovation, technical excellence, and making a difference, this is your opportunity to contribute to Queensland's future. Join DETSI and take the next step in your career!

Applications to remain current for 12 months.

Job Title: Staff Data Engineer ( AI & Analytics Data Products)
Ad Text:
Company Description

About SEEK

SEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities. We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.

Life at SEEK

SEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do. Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Places to Work in Technology (2021-2024). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.

Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting.

Job Description

The Team

The AI & Analytics Data Products team builds high-quality data assets that empower teams across SEEK Group to gain valuable insights and enhance experiences for both individuals and organisations.

This position will report to the Engineering Manager and be part of a team made up of senior and mid-level data engineers. This role collaborates closely with internal peers, including staff, senior, and mid-level data engineers; analytics engineers; data solution designers; and data tracking specialists.

About the role 

The  Staff Data Engineer, is a senior technical leader within the AI & Analytics Data Products team, responsible for building high-quality data assets that empower teams across SEEK Group to deliver insights and enhance experiences for people and organisations.

As an in-team technical specialist, you design and build fit-for-purpose solutions while strengthening the team’s technical systems and platforms. You lead and elevate technical practices that enable effective software delivery, demonstrating deep expertise in the team’s codebase, systems, and tools.

You also drive alignment between your team’s technical roadmap and SEEK’s broader technology strategy.

Responsibilities 

Design, build and operate scalable, high‑performing data platforms and services aligned with SEEK’s technology strategy.
Ensure systems are well‑architected, secure, and meet SEEK’s technical and platform health metrics.
Lead and embed strong engineering and DevOps practices to continuously improve delivery and reliability.
Act as the technical escalation point, owning production issues through to resolution.
Champion clean, well‑tested, secure code and uplift technical capability within the team.
Collaborate effectively with Architecture, Security, and other technical stakeholders to align solutions.
Drive clear communication and alignment between technical work, team priorities, and customer outcomes.
Qualifications

Skills and experience 

Deep expertise in the Spark framework (Batch and Structured Streaming).
Proven experience building and operating large‑scale, cloud‑based data platforms and warehouses.
Strong proficiency with cloud environments (AWS, GCP, or Azure).
Advanced software engineering, coding, scripting, and SQL/database skills.
Skilled in logical and physical data modelling.
Hands‑on experience with DevOps practices — deployments, infrastructure, monitoring, and operations.
Demonstrated leadership in tech‑leading, mentoring, and developing engineers to enhance delivery performance.
Additional Information

Permanent Perks
At SEEK we offer:

Annual Performance Bonus Plan
Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.
Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave
Support for parents with 14 weeks paid primary carers leave and 2 weeks paid leave for partners
SEEK is committed to operating sustainably and is preparing for the impacts of climate change and the transition to a low-carbon future, and is working to minimise its environmental impacts which includes a long-term emissions reduction target of net zero by FY2050

At SEEK, we are passionate about fostering a culture of inclusion and wellbeing that embraces and values the diversity of our people. We are a purpose driven business that works with heart.

We know teams with diverse ideas, experiences and perspectives are more creative and are critical to ensuring effective delivery and innovating to enable our future success. As such, we welcome applications from people with diverse backgrounds and life experiences, especially as they relate to gender, sexual identity, culture, faith, disability and life stages. If you have the skills, curiosity and an adaptable mindset but don't meet every responsibility or qualification listed in this advertisement, please still get in touch with us.

Should you require any specific support or adjustments throughout the recruitment process and beyond, please advise us and we will be happy to assist.

For this role, only those candidates with the eligible right to work will be considered.

SEEK kindly requests no unsolicited resumes or approaches from recruitment agencies and will not be responsible for any associated fees.

Ad Text:
We are seeking an experienced AI & Innovation Engineer to join our Technology Delivery team supporting a strategic AI-powered system.

This role plays a critical part in ensuring the quality, reliability, and performance of modern Machine Learning, Large Language Model (LLM), and Generative AI solutions. You will design and implement scalable automation frameworks across the full technology stack - from React-based user interfaces through to backend services, AI models, search platforms, and data orchestration pipelines.

You will lead testing innovation for AI-driven applications, validating contextual accuracy, factual correctness, and ongoing performance of LLM models while enabling continuous delivery of platform enhancements.

Key Responsibilities

Develop automated testing strategies for ML, LLM, and Generative AI applications

Validate AI outputs for accuracy, relevance, and response quality across multiple models

Integrate automation into CI/CD pipelines to support continuous delivery

Build end-to-end regression and performance test suites

Monitor automation metrics and provide actionable quality insights

Lead test planning, coverage strategy, and risk-based testing activities

Mentor junior engineers and promote automation best practices

Collaborate closely with developers, product teams, and stakeholders

Drive continuous improvement of testing frameworks and DevOps practices

Technical Environment

Languages & Tools: Python, pytest, FastAPI

Automation: Playwright, Selenium, Appium, REST Assured

AI & Data: Azure OpenAI, AWS Bedrock, Databricks, Elasticsearch, Vector Search

Frontend & Backend: React / Next.js, APIs, distributed services

Cloud & DevOps: AWS, Azure, Git, CI/CD pipelines

Skills & Experience

Strong experience designing scalable test automation frameworks

Hands-on testing of AI, NLP, or LLM-based applications

Advanced Python automation development

Experience testing complex distributed systems, APIs, and data platforms

Deep understanding of Agile delivery and DevOps practices

Experience with cloud-based testing environments

Ability to produce meaningful quality metrics and reporting

What You'll Bring

Technical leadership in automation and quality engineering

Strong analytical and problem-solving capability

Passion for emerging AI technologies and innovation

Ability to work autonomously while contributing to high-performing teams

Desirable Certifications

ISTQB Advanced Test Automation Engineering (CTAL-TAE)

AI/ML or Data Science certifications

Python or SQL certifications

Why Join Us?

This is an opportunity to work at the forefront of AI and Generative AI technology, shaping testing practices for next-generation intelligent platforms while delivering meaningful enterprise impact.
